 CSS Grid
Today's Focus: Grid Layout System
What I Learned:

display: grid and grid containers

grid-template-columns, grid-template-rows

grid-gap (now gap)

Grid areas and responsive grid layouts

Practice Exercise: Dashboard layout

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        .dashboard {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
            grid-template-rows: 80px 1fr 60px;
            height: 100vh;
            grid-template-areas:
                "sidebar header"
                "sidebar main"
                "sidebar footer";
        }
        .header {
            grid-area: header;
            background: #3498db;
            padding: 20px;
            color: white;
        }
        .sidebar {
            grid-area: sidebar;
            background: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .main {
            grid-area: main;
            padding: 20px;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
        }
        .footer {
            grid-area: footer;
            background: #ecf0f1;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
        }
        .widget {
            background: #f9f9f9;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .dashboard {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                grid-template-areas:
                    "header"
                    "sidebar"
                    "main"
                    "footer";
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="dashboard">
        <header class="header">
            <h1>Admin Dashboard</h1>
        </header>
        <aside class="sidebar">
            <h3>Menu</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Dashboard</li>
                <li>Users</li>
                <li>Settings</li>
                <li>Reports</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
        <main class="main">
            <div class="widget">Active Users: 150</div>
            <div class="widget">Revenue: $5,200</div>
            <div class="widget">Tasks: 12/15</div>
            <div class="widget">Server Load: 78%</div>
        </main>
        <footer class="footer">
            <p>&copy; 2025 Dashboard. All rights reserved.</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

Practice Question:
Create a photo gallery with CSS Grid:

4 columns on desktop, 2 on tablet, 1 on mobile

Use grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr))

Add hover effect to scale images

Create a masonry layout with grid-auto-rows: 150px

Implement a modal that opens on image click (JavaScript later)
